Note:
Runa Standard Library: Message Passing Channels Module

Provides type-safe message passing channels for communication between threads
and actors. Channels are the primary communication mechanism in Runa's
actor-based concurrency model, offering both synchronous and asynchronous
message passing with various buffering strategies.

Features:
- Unbuffered (synchronous) channels for direct thread communication
- Buffered channels with configurable capacity and overflow strategies
- Multi-producer, multi-consumer (MPMC) channels
- Single-producer, single-consumer (SPSC) optimized channels
- Broadcast channels for one-to-many communication
- Priority channels with message ordering
- Timeout support for all send/receive operations
- Channel closing and completion detection
- Backpressure handling and flow control
- Performance monitoring and statistics
- Integration with Runa's actor model (Send/Receive syntax)
- Memory-efficient lock-free implementations where possible

Channel Types:
- Channel[T]: Basic MPMC channel with optional buffering
- SPSCChannel[T]: Optimized single-producer, single-consumer channel
- BroadcastChannel[T]: One-to-many broadcast communication
- PriorityChannel[T]: Priority-ordered message delivery
- UnboundedChannel[T]: Dynamically growing channel buffer

Thread Safety: All channel operations are thread-safe and designed
for high-performance concurrent access patterns.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/concurrent/atomic" as atomic

Note: Core Channel Types
Type Channel[T] is Dictionary with:
    buffer as List[T] defaults to list containing
    capacity as Integer defaults to 0
    size as Integer defaults to 0
    closed as Boolean defaults to false
    senders_waiting as Integer defaults to 0
    receivers_waiting as Integer defaults to 0
    total_sent as Integer defaults to 0
    total_received as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    send_timeouts as Integer defaults to 0
    receive_timeouts as Integer defaults to 0
    overflow_strategy as String defaults to "block"
    channel_type as String defaults to "mpmc"
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type SPSCChannel[T] is Dictionary with:
    buffer as List[T] defaults to list containing
    capacity as Integer defaults to 1024
    head as Integer defaults to 0
    tail as Integer defaults to 0
    closed as Boolean defaults to false
    total_sent as Integer defaults to 0
    total_received as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    cache_line_padding as List[Integer] defaults to list containing
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type BroadcastChannel[T] is Dictionary with:
    buffer as List[T] defaults to list containing
    capacity as Integer defaults to 1024
    write_position as Integer defaults to 0
    closed as Boolean defaults to false
    subscribers as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    total_sent as Integer defaults to 0
    total_broadcasts as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type PriorityChannel[T] is Dictionary with:
    priority_queue as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    capacity as Integer defaults to 0
    size as Integer defaults to 0
    closed as Boolean defaults to false
    senders_waiting as Integer defaults to 0
    receivers_waiting as Integer defaults to 0
    total_sent as Integer defaults to 0
    total_received as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type ChannelResult[T] is:
    | ChannelSuccess with value as T and delivery_time as Float
    | ChannelTimeout with elapsed_time as Float
    | ChannelClosed with error_message as String
    | ChannelFull with capacity as Integer and current_size as Integer
    | ChannelException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type SendResult is:
    | SendSuccess with delivery_time as Float and queue_position as Integer
    | SendTimeout with elapsed_time as Float and queue_size as Integer
    | SendClosed with error_message as String
    | SendFull with capacity as Integer and overflow_action as String
    | SendException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type ReceiveResult[T] is:
    | ReceiveSuccess with value as T and wait_time as Float
    | ReceiveTimeout with elapsed_time as Float and queue_size as Integer
    | ReceiveClosed with error_message as String
    | ReceiveEmpty
    | ReceiveException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type BroadcastSubscriber is Dictionary with:
    subscriber_id as String
    read_position as Integer defaults to 0
    active as Boolean defaults to true
    total_received as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Basic Channel Operations
Process called "create_channel" that takes capacity as Integer and overflow_strategy as Optional[String] returns Channel[Any]:
    If capacity is less than 0:
        Throw "Channel capacity must be non-negative, got: " plus capacity as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_overflow_strategy be overflow_strategy if overflow_strategy is not None else "block"
    
    Let valid_strategies be list containing "block", "drop_newest", "drop_oldest", "error"
    If not valid_strategies contains final_overflow_strategy:
        Throw "Invalid overflow strategy: " plus final_overflow_strategy plus ". Must be one of: " plus join_list with list as valid_strategies and separator as ", "
    
    Let channel be Channel[Any] with:
        buffer as list containing
        capacity as capacity
        size as 0
        closed as false
        senders_waiting as 0
        receivers_waiting as 0
        total_sent as 0
        total_received as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        send_timeouts as 0
        receive_timeouts as 0
        overflow_strategy as final_overflow_strategy
        channel_type as "mpmc"
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "channel_factory"
    
    Let result be initialize_channel_synchronization with channel as channel
    If not result.success:
        Throw "Failed to initialize channel synchronization: " plus result.error_message
    
    Return channel

Process called "send_to_channel" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and value as Any and timeout as Optional[Float] returns SendResult:
    If channel.closed:
        Return SendClosed with error_message as "Cannot send to closed channel"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if channel has capacity
        If channel.capacity is equal to 0:
            Note: Unbuffered channel - need direct handoff
            Let handoff_result be attempt_direct_handoff with:
                channel as channel
                value as value
                timeout as timeout
            
            Match handoff_result.status:
                When "success":
                    Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
                    Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                    Return SendSuccess with:
                        delivery_time as delivery_time
                        queue_position as 0
                
                When "timeout":
                    Set channel.send_timeouts to channel.send_timeouts plus 1
                    Let elapsed_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                    Return SendTimeout with:
                        elapsed_time as elapsed_time
                        queue_size as channel.size
                
                When "closed":
                    Return SendClosed with error_message as "Channel closed during send"
                
                Otherwise:
                    Return SendException with:
                        error_message as "Unknown handoff result: " plus handoff_result.status
                        error_code as "CHANNEL_UNKNOWN_HANDOFF"
        
        Else If channel.size is less than channel.capacity:
            Note: Buffered channel with space available
            Let buffer_result be add_to_channel_buffer with:
                channel as channel
                value as value
            
            If buffer_result.success:
                Set channel.size to channel.size plus 1
                Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
                
                Note: Notify waiting receivers
                Let notify_result be notify_channel_receivers with channel as channel
                
                Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return SendSuccess with:
                    delivery_time as delivery_time
                    queue_position as channel.size
            Otherwise:
                Return SendException with:
                    error_message as "Failed to add to buffer: " plus buffer_result.error_message
                    error_code as "CHANNEL_BUFFER_ERROR"
        
        Otherwise:
            Note: Channel is full - handle according to overflow strategy
            Match channel.overflow_strategy:
                When "block":
                    Let wait_result be wait_for_channel_space with:
                        channel as channel
                        value as value
                        timeout as timeout
                    
                    Match wait_result.status:
                        When "success":
                            Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
                            Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                            Return SendSuccess with:
                                delivery_time as delivery_time
                                queue_position as channel.size
                        
                        When "timeout":
                            Set channel.send_timeouts to channel.send_timeouts plus 1
                            Let elapsed_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                            Return SendTimeout with:
                                elapsed_time as elapsed_time
                                queue_size as channel.size
                        
                        When "closed":
                            Return SendClosed with error_message as "Channel closed while waiting"
                        
                        Otherwise:
                            Return SendException with:
                                error_message as "Unknown wait result: " plus wait_result.status
                                error_code as "CHANNEL_UNKNOWN_WAIT"
                
                When "drop_newest":
                    Note: Drop the new message
                    Return SendFull with:
                        capacity as channel.capacity
                        overflow_action as "dropped_newest"
                
                When "drop_oldest":
                    Note: Remove oldest message and add new one
                    Let drop_result be drop_oldest_from_channel with channel as channel
                    If drop_result.success:
                        Let add_result be add_to_channel_buffer with:
                            channel as channel
                            value as value
                        
                        If add_result.success:
                            Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
                            Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                            Return SendSuccess with:
                                delivery_time as delivery_time
                                queue_position as channel.size
                        Otherwise:
                            Return SendException with:
                                error_message as "Failed to add after drop: " plus add_result.error_message
                                error_code as "CHANNEL_DROP_ADD_ERROR"
                    Otherwise:
                        Return SendException with:
                            error_message as "Failed to drop oldest: " plus drop_result.error_message
                            error_code as "CHANNEL_DROP_ERROR"
                
                When "error":
                    Return SendFull with:
                        capacity as channel.capacity
                        overflow_action as "error_on_full"
                
                Otherwise:
                    Return SendException with:
                        error_message as "Unknown overflow strategy: " plus channel.overflow_strategy
                        error_code as "CHANNEL_UNKNOWN_STRATEGY"
    
    Catch error:
        Return SendException with:
            error_message as "Send exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "CHANNEL_SEND_EXCEPTION"

Process called "receive_from_channel" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns ReceiveResult[Any]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if channel has messages available
        If channel.size is greater than 0:
            Let message_result be remove_from_channel_buffer with channel as channel
            If message_result.success:
                Set channel.size to channel.size minus 1
                Set channel.total_received to channel.total_received plus 1
                
                Note: Notify waiting senders
                Let notify_result be notify_channel_senders with channel as channel
                
                Let wait_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return ReceiveSuccess with:
                    value as message_result.value
                    wait_time as wait_time
            Otherwise:
                Return ReceiveException with:
                    error_message as "Failed to remove from buffer: " plus message_result.error_message
                    error_code as "CHANNEL_BUFFER_REMOVE_ERROR"
        
        Else If channel.closed:
            Return ReceiveClosed with error_message as "Channel is closed and empty"
        
        Otherwise:
            Note: No messages available - wait for one
            Let wait_result be wait_for_channel_message with:
                channel as channel
                timeout as timeout
            
            Match wait_result.status:
                When "success":
                    Set channel.total_received to channel.total_received plus 1
                    Let wait_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                    Return ReceiveSuccess with:
                        value as wait_result.value
                        wait_time as wait_time
                
                When "timeout":
                    Set channel.receive_timeouts to channel.receive_timeouts plus 1
                    Let elapsed_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                    Return ReceiveTimeout with:
                        elapsed_time as elapsed_time
                        queue_size as channel.size
                
                When "closed":
                    Return ReceiveClosed with error_message as "Channel closed while waiting"
                
                Otherwise:
                    Return ReceiveException with:
                        error_message as "Unknown wait result: " plus wait_result.status
                        error_code as "CHANNEL_UNKNOWN_WAIT"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ReceiveException with:
            error_message as "Receive exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "CHANNEL_RECEIVE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "close_channel" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns None:
    Try:
        Set channel.closed to true
        
        Note: Wake all waiting senders and receivers
        Let wake_senders_result be wake_all_channel_senders with channel as channel
        Let wake_receivers_result be wake_all_channel_receivers with channel as channel
        
        Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "Failed to close channel: " plus error.message

Process called "is_channel_closed" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return channel.closed

Process called "get_channel_size" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Integer:
    Return channel.size

Process called "get_channel_capacity" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Integer:
    Return channel.capacity

Process called "is_channel_empty" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return channel.size is equal to 0

Process called "is_channel_full" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Boolean:
    If channel.capacity is equal to 0:
        Return false  Note: Unbuffered channels are never "full"
    Return channel.size is equal to channel.capacity
:End Note

Note: Single-Producer Single-Consumer (SPSC) Channel Operations
Process called "create_spsc_channel" that takes capacity as Integer returns SPSCChannel[Any]:
    If capacity is less than 1:
        Throw "SPSC channel capacity must be positive, got: " plus capacity as String
    
    Note: Ensure capacity is power of 2 for efficient modulo operations
    Let adjusted_capacity be next_power_of_two with value as capacity
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let spsc_channel be SPSCChannel[Any] with:
        buffer as create_list_with_size with size as adjusted_capacity
        capacity as adjusted_capacity
        head as 0
        tail as 0
        closed as false
        total_sent as 0
        total_received as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        cache_line_padding as create_list_with_size with size as 64  Note: Cache line alignment
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "spsc_channel_factory"
    
    Return spsc_channel

Process called "spsc_send" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] and value as Any returns SendResult:
    If channel.closed:
        Return SendClosed with error_message as "Cannot send to closed SPSC channel"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Let next_tail be (channel.tail plus 1) modulo channel.capacity
        
        Note: Check if channel is full
        If next_tail is equal to channel.head:
            Return SendFull with:
                capacity as channel.capacity
                overflow_action as "spsc_full"
        
        Note: Add message to buffer
        Set channel.buffer[channel.tail] to value
        Set channel.tail to next_tail
        Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
        
        Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        Return SendSuccess with:
            delivery_time as delivery_time
            queue_position as (channel.tail minus channel.head plus channel.capacity) modulo channel.capacity
    
    Catch error:
        Return SendException with:
            error_message as "SPSC send exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "SPSC_SEND_EXCEPTION"

Process called "spsc_receive" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] returns ReceiveResult[Any]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if channel is empty
        If channel.head is equal to channel.tail:
            If channel.closed:
                Return ReceiveClosed with error_message as "SPSC channel is closed and empty"
            Otherwise:
                Return ReceiveEmpty
        
        Note: Get message from buffer
        Let value be channel.buffer[channel.head]
        Set channel.head to (channel.head plus 1) modulo channel.capacity
        Set channel.total_received to channel.total_received plus 1
        
        Let wait_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        Return ReceiveSuccess with:
            value as value
            wait_time as wait_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return ReceiveException with:
            error_message as "SPSC receive exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "SPSC_RECEIVE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "close_spsc_channel" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] returns None:
    Set channel.closed to true
    Return None

Process called "is_spsc_channel_empty" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return channel.head is equal to channel.tail

Process called "is_spsc_channel_full" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] returns Boolean:
    Let next_tail be (channel.tail plus 1) modulo channel.capacity
    Return next_tail is equal to channel.head

Process called "get_spsc_channel_size" that takes channel as SPSCChannel[Any] returns Integer:
    Return (channel.tail minus channel.head plus channel.capacity) modulo channel.capacity
:End Note

Note: Broadcast Channel Operations
Process called "create_broadcast_channel" that takes capacity as Integer returns BroadcastChannel[Any]:
    If capacity is less than 1:
        Throw "Broadcast channel capacity must be positive, got: " plus capacity as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let broadcast_channel be BroadcastChannel[Any] with:
        buffer as create_list_with_size with size as capacity
        capacity as capacity
        write_position as 0
        closed as false
        subscribers as list containing
        total_sent as 0
        total_broadcasts as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "broadcast_channel_factory"
    
    Return broadcast_channel

Process called "broadcast_send" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] and value as Any returns SendResult:
    If channel.closed:
        Return SendClosed with error_message as "Cannot send to closed broadcast channel"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Add message to circular buffer
        Set channel.buffer[channel.write_position modulo channel.capacity] to value
        Set channel.write_position to channel.write_position plus 1
        Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
        Set channel.total_broadcasts to channel.total_broadcasts plus 1
        
        Note: Clean up subscribers that are too far behind
        Let cleanup_result be cleanup_lagging_subscribers with channel as channel
        
        Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        Return SendSuccess with:
            delivery_time as delivery_time
            queue_position as channel.write_position
    
    Catch error:
        Return SendException with:
            error_message as "Broadcast send exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BROADCAST_SEND_EXCEPTION"

Process called "subscribe_to_broadcast" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] and subscriber_id as String returns BroadcastSubscriber:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let subscriber be BroadcastSubscriber with:
        subscriber_id as subscriber_id
        read_position as channel.write_position  Note: Start from current position
        active as true
        total_received as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        metadata as dictionary containing "subscribed_to" as "broadcast_channel"
    
    Add subscriber to channel.subscribers
    
    Return subscriber

Process called "broadcast_receive" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] and subscriber as BroadcastSubscriber returns ReceiveResult[Any]:
    If not subscriber.active:
        Return ReceiveException with:
            error_message as "Subscriber is not active"
            error_code as "BROADCAST_INACTIVE_SUBSCRIBER"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if there are unread messages
        If subscriber.read_position is equal to channel.write_position:
            If channel.closed:
                Return ReceiveClosed with error_message as "Broadcast channel is closed"
            Otherwise:
                Return ReceiveEmpty
        
        Note: Check if subscriber is too far behind
        Let messages_behind be channel.write_position minus subscriber.read_position
        If messages_behind is greater than channel.capacity:
            Note: Subscriber missed messages, move to oldest available
            Set subscriber.read_position to channel.write_position minus channel.capacity
        
        Note: Get next message
        Let buffer_index be subscriber.read_position modulo channel.capacity
        Let value be channel.buffer[buffer_index]
        Set subscriber.read_position to subscriber.read_position plus 1
        Set subscriber.total_received to subscriber.total_received plus 1
        
        Let wait_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        Return ReceiveSuccess with:
            value as value
            wait_time as wait_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return ReceiveException with:
            error_message as "Broadcast receive exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BROADCAST_RECEIVE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "unsubscribe_from_broadcast" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] and subscriber as BroadcastSubscriber returns None:
    Set subscriber.active to false
    
    Note: Remove subscriber from channel's subscriber list
    Let filtered_subscribers be list containing
    For each sub in channel.subscribers:
        If sub.subscriber_id is not equal to subscriber.subscriber_id:
            Add sub to filtered_subscribers
    
    Set channel.subscribers to filtered_subscribers
    Return None

Process called "get_broadcast_subscriber_count" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] returns Integer:
    Let active_count be 0
    For each subscriber in channel.subscribers:
        If subscriber.active:
            Set active_count to active_count plus 1
    Return active_count
:End Note

Note: Priority Channel Operations
Process called "create_priority_channel" that takes capacity as Integer returns PriorityChannel[Any]:
    If capacity is less than 0:
        Throw "Priority channel capacity must be non-negative, got: " plus capacity as String
    
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let priority_channel be PriorityChannel[Any] with:
        priority_queue as list containing
        capacity as capacity
        size as 0
        closed as false
        senders_waiting as 0
        receivers_waiting as 0
        total_sent as 0
        total_received as 0
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "priority_channel_factory"
    
    Return priority_channel

Process called "priority_send" that takes channel as PriorityChannel[Any] and value as Any and priority as Integer returns SendResult:
    If channel.closed:
        Return SendClosed with error_message as "Cannot send to closed priority channel"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        If channel.capacity is greater than 0 and channel.size is greater than or equal to channel.capacity:
            Return SendFull with:
                capacity as channel.capacity
                overflow_action as "priority_full"
        
        Note: Create priority message
        Let priority_message be dictionary containing:
            "value" as value
            "priority" as priority
            "timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
            "sequence" as channel.total_sent
        
        Note: Insert into priority queue (higher priority first)
        Let insert_result be insert_into_priority_queue with:
            queue as channel.priority_queue
            message as priority_message
        
        If insert_result.success:
            Set channel.size to channel.size plus 1
            Set channel.total_sent to channel.total_sent plus 1
            
            Note: Notify waiting receivers
            Let notify_result be notify_priority_channel_receivers with channel as channel
            
            Let delivery_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
            Return SendSuccess with:
                delivery_time as delivery_time
                queue_position as insert_result.position
        Otherwise:
            Return SendException with:
                error_message as "Failed to insert into priority queue: " plus insert_result.error_message
                error_code as "PRIORITY_INSERT_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return SendException with:
            error_message as "Priority send exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "PRIORITY_SEND_EXCEPTION"

Process called "priority_receive" that takes channel as PriorityChannel[Any] returns ReceiveResult[Any]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        If channel.size is equal to 0:
            If channel.closed:
                Return ReceiveClosed with error_message as "Priority channel is closed and empty"
            Otherwise:
                Return ReceiveEmpty
        
        Note: Remove highest priority message
        Let remove_result be remove_from_priority_queue with queue as channel.priority_queue
        If remove_result.success:
            Set channel.size to channel.size minus 1
            Set channel.total_received to channel.total_received plus 1
            
            Note: Notify waiting senders
            Let notify_result be notify_priority_channel_senders with channel as channel
            
            Let wait_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
            Return ReceiveSuccess with:
                value as remove_result.message.value
                wait_time as wait_time
        Otherwise:
            Return ReceiveException with:
                error_message as "Failed to remove from priority queue: " plus remove_result.error_message
                error_code as "PRIORITY_REMOVE_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return ReceiveException with:
            error_message as "Priority receive exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "PRIORITY_RECEIVE_EXCEPTION"
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "get_channel_statistics" that takes channel as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "capacity" as channel.capacity
        "size" as channel.size
        "closed" as channel.closed
        "total_sent" as channel.total_sent
        "total_received" as channel.total_received
        "send_timeouts" as channel.send_timeouts
        "receive_timeouts" as channel.receive_timeouts
        "creation_timestamp" as channel.creation_timestamp
        "uptime_seconds" as get_current_timestamp minus channel.creation_timestamp
        "throughput_sent" as channel.total_sent divided by (get_current_timestamp minus channel.creation_timestamp plus 1.0)
        "throughput_received" as channel.total_received divided by (get_current_timestamp minus channel.creation_timestamp plus 1.0)

Process called "next_power_of_two" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let power be 1
    While power is less than value:
        Set power to power times 2
    Return power

Process called "create_list_with_size" that takes size as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For i from 0 to size minus 1:
        Add None to result
    Return result

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds


Note: Low-level Channel Implementation Functions (Platform-dependent)
Process called "initialize_channel_synchronization" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize platform-specific channel synchronization primitives
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "attempt_direct_handoff" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and value as Any and timeout as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Attempt direct handoff for unbuffered channel
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "success"

Process called "add_to_channel_buffer" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Add message to channel buffer
    Add value to channel.buffer
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "remove_from_channel_buffer" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Remove message from channel buffer
    If length of channel.buffer is greater than 0:
        Let value be channel.buffer[0]
        Set channel.buffer to channel.buffer[1:]
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as value, "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as None, "error_message" as "Buffer is empty"

Process called "drop_oldest_from_channel" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Drop oldest message from channel buffer
    If length of channel.buffer is greater than 0:
        Set channel.buffer to channel.buffer[1:]
        Set channel.size to channel.size minus 1
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "error_message" as "No messages to drop"

Process called "wait_for_channel_space" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and value as Any and timeout as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for space in channel buffer
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "success"

Process called "wait_for_channel_message" that takes channel as Channel[Any] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for message in channel
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "timeout"

Process called "notify_channel_receivers" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Notify waiting receivers that message is available
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "notify_channel_senders" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Notify waiting senders that space is available
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "wake_all_channel_senders" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wake all threads waiting to send
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "wake_all_channel_receivers" that takes channel as Channel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wake all threads waiting to receive
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "cleanup_lagging_subscribers" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Remove subscribers that are too far behind
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "insert_into_priority_queue" that takes queue as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] and message as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Insert message into priority queue maintaining order
    Add message to queue
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "position" as length of queue, "error_message" as ""

Process called "remove_from_priority_queue" that takes queue as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Remove highest priority message from queue
    If length of queue is greater than 0:
        Let message be queue[0]
        Set queue to queue[1:]
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "message" as message, "error_message" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "message" as None, "error_message" as "Queue is empty"

Process called "notify_priority_channel_receivers" that takes channel as PriorityChannel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Notify waiting receivers in priority channel
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "notify_priority_channel_senders" that takes channel as PriorityChannel[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Notify waiting senders in priority channel
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""
:End Note